	(270,58,'cf_06_04','EOC 4','Reporting any problem to the supplier and /or referring physician of changes in condition or general health.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(271,59,'cf_07_01','EOC 1','Provide appropriate beneficiary follow-up care consistent with the items or services provided, the patient’s diagnosis, specific care rendered and recommendations. Review and make changes to treatment plan based on patient’s current condition.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(272,59,'cf_07_02','EOC 2','All follow-up communication is documented in the patient’s file.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(273,59,'cf_07_03','EOC 3','The patient/caregiver is informed of the procedures for repairing, replacing, and/or adjusting the device or items, the possible risks, and estimated time involved in the process.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(274,59,'cf_07_04','EOC 4','Have access to the equipment (or another provider who has it) needed to modify or adjust the item.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(275,59,'cf_07_05','EOC 5','Patient is advised to contact the prescribing physician as appropriate for the use of the specific items or service.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(276,59,'cf_07_06','EOC 6','Follow-up is performed within 1 week of delivery. Follow-up is continued until item reaches optimal level of fit and function.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(277,60,'reg_01_01','EOC 1','Supplier shall have a physical location and display all licenses, certificates and permits to operate. These must be posted in an area accessible to all customer. Upon request, copies shall be provided to government officials or their agents (including The Compliance Team, Inc.)','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(278,60,'reg_01_02','EOC 2','Licenses must be present for each State where the company is doing business (unless not required by the State). If mail order, a spreadsheet (or copies) with all of the licenses and expirations dates must be available for review.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(279,60,'reg_01_03','EOC 3','Supplier Standards, Federal and State posting must be present.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(280,60,'reg_01_04','EOC 4','Facility must be American Disability Act Complaint.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(281,60,'reg_01_05','EOC 5','Provide is in Compliance with all Medicare Standards.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(282,60,'reg_01_06','EOC 6','All exits are marked with signs.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(283,60,'reg_01_01_ss_fire','EOC 1','Fire extinguisher is mounted and has been checked and approved for use.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(284,60,'reg_01_02_ss_fire','EOC 2','An in-service for all employees on Fire safety and how to operate an extinguisher is performed annually. Documentation is maintained either in the personnel file or training file.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(285,60,'reg_01_03_ss_fire','EOC 3','All staff has written documentation of attendance at Fire Safety in-service.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(286,61,'reg_02.a_01','EOC 1','The organization has a written work-exposure plan. Environmental Housekeeping Schedule is posted on the Cleaning Area.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(287,61,'reg_02.a_02','EOC 2','Staff members who are identified for being at risk have been offered Hepatitis B vaccinations and have either accepted at the employer’s expense, or have signed a letter of declination. If employee declines initially, they can accept at a later date at the employer’s expense.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(288,61,'reg_02.a_03','EOC 3','The staff members who are at risk for exposure have been trained on the OSHA standard (annually) and have written documentation in their personnel file.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(289,61,'reg_02.a_04','EOC 4','Personal Protective equipment is available and accessible to the appropriate staff for their use.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(290,62,'reg_02.b_01','EOC 1','The organization determines if they service a patient population that is high risk for TB and/or are in a geography that has a higher risk for TB.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(291,62,'reg_02.b_02','EOC 2','<p>If at risk, the organization does the following:</p>\n<ul>\r<li>Develops and implements a respiratory protection plan.</li>\r<li>Has Hepa-filter (N-95) fit tested masks available for those employees with patient contact.</li>\n<li>All staff with patient contact must have a TB skin test and a medical evaluation.</li>\r<li>Employees are trained in respiratory protection, annually.</li>\n</ul>','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(292,62,'reg_02.b_03','EOC 3','OSHA Tuberculosis (TB) Training of staff at risk is performed annually and documented in the personnel files.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(293,63,'reg_02.c_01','EOC 1','The organization provides training to all employees on OSHA’s Right to Know and training is documented in the personnel file, annually.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(294,63,'reg_02.c_02','EOC 2','Material Safety Data Sheets are filed for all hazardous material in the organization’s workplace and employees are knowledgeable of the location. (e.g. cleaning disinfectants, chemicals, lubricants, toner, etc.)','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(295,63,'reg_02.c_03','EOC 3','The organization contacts OSHA and posts all mandatory posters that are received.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(296,64,'reg_02.d_01','EOC 1','<p>The organization has an organized process for handling an on-site emergency, (e.g. Fire) which addresses the following:</p>\n<ul>\r<li>How employees will be notified of emergency</li>\r<li>Staff responsible for calling the Fire Department</li>\r<li>Emergency use of Fire extinguishers if warranted</li>\r<li>Location of where employees should meet outside the building</li>\r<li>Staff person designated to do head count upon evacuation of the building</li>\n</ul>','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(297,64,'reg_02.d_02','EOC 2','<p>The organization has an organized process for handling an off-site emergency, (e.g. Snowstorm, flood etc.) which addresses the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>How employees will be notified of emergency</li>\r<li>Staff responsible for notification and triaging of patient services</li>\r<li>If product or equipment is necessary for sustaining patient’s health or life, emergency services are arranged to ensure continuation of services</li>\r<li>Contingency plan includes alternative provider in the event that the organization cannot service its own customers.</li>\n</ul>','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(298,64,'reg_02.d_03','EOC 3','The personnel records reflect documentation of annual training of staff on emergency preparedness.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(299,65,'reg_03.a_01','EOC 1','The organization shall obtain manufacturer copies of the features, warranties, and instructions for each type of non-custom-fabricated item.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(300,65,'reg_03.a_02','EOC 2','Organization has a mechanism in place to prevent using products that are non adulterated, counterfeit, suspected of being counterfeit and have been obtained by fraud or deceit and to ensure that the products are not misbranded.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(301,65,'reg_03.a_03','EOC 3','All products are appropriately labeled for their intended distribution channels.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(302,66,'reg_03.b_01','EOC 1','Written (or electronic) registration with the FDA is available for review.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(303,66,'reg_03.b_02','EOC 2','FDA Registrations must be completed prior to any initial or renewal visits with The Compliance Team, Inc.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(304,66,'reg_03.b_01_ss_resp','EOC 1','The organization is registered with the state (if applicable).','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(305,66,'reg_03.b_02_ss_resp','EOC 2','<p>The organization has a written policy and procedure for the following:</p>\n<ul>\r<li>Inspection, use and storage of oxygen both liquid and gas</li>\r<li>Testing for bulk delivery from supplier, for vehicle mounted cryogenic vessels, for Dewars delivered by the supplier to the HME, for refilling of cryogenics home unit, for cryogenic home units and for compressed gases.</li>\n</ul>','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(306,66,'reg_03.b_03_ss_resp','EOC 3','Oxygen analyzers are calibrated according to manufacturer guidelines and a log is maintained.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(307,66,'reg_03.b_04_ss_resp','EOC 4','A separate consumer complaint file for Oxygen is maintained.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(308,66,'reg_03.b_05_ss_resp','EOC 5','The organization trains the staff responsible for the transfilling annually and is documented in personnel file.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(309,66,'reg_03.b_06_ss_resp','EOC 6','The organization has a written recall procedure.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(310,66,'reg_03.b_07_ss_resp','EOC 7','The organization is able to reconcile the batch or lot number and the purity test completed on each batch or lot.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(311,66,'reg_03.b_08_ss_resp','EOC 8','<p>The organization has the following Personal Protective equipment available:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Face shields (liquid oxygen filling)</li>\r<li>Leather gloves (liquid oxygen filling)</li>\r<li>Protective footgear if lifting oxygen cylinders or LOX tanks</li>\n</ul>','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(312,67,'reg_03.c_01','EOC 1','The organization investigates serious patient incidents within 24 hours and is documented.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(313,67,'reg_03.c_02','EOC 2','There is further documentation if a Medical Device Report has been sent to the FDA.','2012-01-01',1,NULL),
	(314,67,'reg_03.c_03','EOC 3','Appropriate employees are trained on such policies and knowledgeable.','2012-01-01',1,NULL);
